"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d9d021",
"children":[
"Vaginitis is characterized by vaginal irritation, pruritus, pain, malodor, or unusual discharge. The three most common infectious causes of acute vaginitis are bacterial vaginosis, vulvovaginal candidiasis, and ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Trichomonas"
]
},
". ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Trichomoniasis is the only cause of vaginitis that is sexually transmitted."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s48_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
