{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ed7cf1",
"children":[
"Because vaginal yeast is found in 10% to 20% of healthy women, the identification of ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Candida"
]
},
" species in patients without symptoms does not require treatment."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s48_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9d0683",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 21-year-old woman has a vaginal discharge and odor. Pelvic examination shows a thin, white homogeneous vaginal discharge with a normal cervix and normal vaginal mucosa. Wet mount is negative for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Trichomonas"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Candida"
]
},
". Vaginal pH is 6.0."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"40cd05",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose bacterial vaginosis."
]
}
]
}
]
},
